events.text:
Day 420
I feel like there should be some kind of significance to this day, but it’s been so long that I’ve forgotten what it could be.
My friends back at home would know.
I wonder what they’re up to now.
Have they started families while I’m up here on this old rock?
Do they still get together every Saturday night for mini golf?
Mini golf is fun, but who actually goes every weekend?
We only play the same course.
It’s too much mini golf!
Though, I suppose it’s less about the mini golf and more about who you’re mini golfing with.
I miss them.
The moon bunny is of small comfort, but it’s better than nothing.
I wonder if moon rocks would make good golf balls.
If only I had pockets.
